  "body": "- [x] I've discussed with @gnidan before filing this issue. https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/pull/5782 might solve this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nIâ€™m trying to start the debugger using `truffle test --debug` as described in [1]. I have created a test case that calls `debug`, run it with `truffle test --debug` but I get\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n  1) Contract: HelloBlockchain\r\n       should succeed debugging:\r\n     TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'currentRunnable')\r\n      at /opt/homebrew/lib/node_modules/truffle/build/webpack:/packages/core/lib/commands/test/prepareConfigAndRunTests.js:23:1\r\n      at Context.<anonymous> (test/TestHelloBlockchain.js:20:11)\r\n      at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nCreate a new box\r\n\r\n```sh\r\ntruffle unbox vscode-starter-box\r\n```\r\n\r\nand add the following test to `test/TestHelloBlockchain.js`, notice the `debug` magic function that allows you to debug tests\r\n\r\n```js\r\n  it(\"should succeed debugging\", async function () {\r\n    const helloBlockchainInstance = await HelloBlockchain.deployed();\r\n    await debug(helloBlockchainInstance.SendRequest(\"Hello Blockchain\", { from: accounts[0] }));\r\n  });\r\n```\r\n\r\nthen run it with\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nganache # in another terminal\r\ntruffle test --debug\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\n> Truffle will interrupt the normal test flow and start the debugger[1]\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: macOS Ventura `13.0.1`\r\n* Ethereum client: `Ganache v7.5.0`\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): `Truffle v5.6.6 (core: 5.6.6)`\r\n* node version (`node --version`): `Node v16.18.0`\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): `8.19.2`\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n[1] https://trufflesuite.com/docs/truffle/how-to/debug-test/use-the-truffle-debugger/#in-test-debugging",
